 <text>
  <front>
   <head>To a Young LADY, who had a CUPID given Her.</head>
  </front>
  <body>
   <lg xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="poem">
    <lg n="1" stanza_type="couplet">
     <l n="1" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">FAIR Lady, take a special Care,</l>
     <l n="2" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">This pleasing Toy become no Snare;</l>
     <l n="3" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">The  is full of Wiles,</l>
     <l n="4" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">And mischiefs most, when most he smiles:</l>
     <l n="5" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Beware to clasp him in your Arms,</l>
     <l n="6" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Nor gaze too much upon his Charms;</l>
     <l n="7" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Lest in a borrow'd Shape he wound,</l>
     <l n="8" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">As once unhappy DIDO found;</l>
     <l n="9" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">For, while she view'd his smiling Look,</l>
     <l n="10" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Her Heart receiv'd a fatal Stroke.</l>
    </lg>
   </lg>
